      { type: "h3", text: "Over investing in polish while under investing in positioning" },
      { type: "p", text: "Beautiful capsules, trailers, and screenshots matter. But they enhance clarity. They do not replace it." },
      { type: "p", text: "If players cannot immediately understand why the game exists and who it is for, polish only increases confusion." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Expecting Early Access to solve wishlist problems" },
      { type: "p", text: "Steam early access wishlist growth is often misunderstood." },
      { type: "p", text: "Early access can boost engagement and gather feedback. It doesn't automatically generate new demand." },
      { type: "p", text: "Without a clear story about why early access matters, it rarely causes a significant wishlist spike." },
      { type: "h2", text: "The system behind effective marketing for video games on Steam" },
      { type: "p", text: "To consistently grow wishlists and generate launch spikes, you need to think in terms of systems, not just campaigns." },
      { type: "p", text: "The system consists of five interconnected layers that develop over time." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Layer one. Audience intent mapping" },
      { type: "p", text: "Not all players are equal when it comes to your launch." },
      { type: "p", text: "You need to identify the specific player segments most likely to wishlist and later convert." },
      { type: "p", text: "This includes genre enthusiasts, fans of similar games, and players driven by particular mechanics or themes." },
      { type: "p", text: "This isn't about demographics; it's about player intent." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Layer two. Core promise clarity" },
      { type: "p", text: "Every successful Steam page delivers one main promise." },
      { type: "p", text: "What experience will this game provide better or differently than others in the genre?" },
      { type: "p", text: "This promise must be immediately clear through visuals, copy, and tags." },
      { type: "p", text: "Without a clear promise, traffic arrives confused and leaves undecided." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Layer three. Contextual traffic sources" },
      { type: "p", text: "Traffic should originate from sources where the promise already feels credible." },
      { type: "p", text: "Genre communities. Niche creators. Subreddits. Discords. Events." },
      { type: "p", text: "This is how the 'coming soon' wishlist strategy on Steam builds warm traffic instead of cold impressions." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Layer four. Conversion focused page structure" },
      { type: "p", text: "The Steam page needs to support the decision-making process." },
      { type: "p", text: "Clear hook. Visual proof. Social validation. Mechanical clarity. Emotional payoff." },
      { type: "p", text: "Each section should answer a question players subconsciously ask before wishlisting." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Layer five. Timed momentum windows" },
      { type: "p", text: "Wishlist spikes are driven, not found." },
      { type: "p", text: "Demos, festivals, updates, creator coverage, and announcements should align within momentum windows." },
      { type: "p", text: "Steam reacts to velocity, not slow buildup." },
      { type: "h2", text: "How steam pre launch wishlist strategy actually works" },
      { type: "p", text: "Pre-launch is not a single phase; it has multiple stages." },
      { type: "p", text: "Understanding these stages is crucial for marketing video games on Steam." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Early pre launch. Foundation stage" },
      { type: "p", text: "This stage starts when the Steam page goes live." },
      { type: "p", text: "The goal isn't to scale but to ensure signal quality." },
      { type: "p", text: "You experiment with positioning. You improve messaging. You determine which audiences convert best." },
      { type: "p", text: "Wishlist growth is intentionally slow." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Mid pre launch. Validation stage" },
      { type: "p", text: "Start increasing exposure selectively." },
      { type: "p", text: "Festivals, playtests, targeted creator outreach." },
      { type: "p", text: "The aim is to verify that the system functions beyond your immediate circle." },
      { type: "p", text: "Conversion rate is more important than volume." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Late pre launch. Momentum stage" },
      { type: "p", text: "This is where a Steam wishlist spike before launch becomes possible." },
      { type: "p", text: "You cluster updates, coverage, demos, and announcements." },
      { type: "p", text: "The goal is to generate sustained wishlist momentum over days, not just isolated spikes." },
      { type: "p", text: "Steam algorithms recognize consistency." },
      { type: "h2", text: "Steam launch wishlist spike and why timing matters more than volume" },
      { type: "p", text: "Many teams believe they need one massive event to create a spike." },
      { type: "p", text: "In reality, spikes often result from consistent pressure over a short period." },
      { type: "p", text: "Multiple creators releasing content about the game within the same week. A demo update followed by a new feature. A festival succeeded by a major announcement." },
      { type: "p", text: "This pattern builds player confidence and trust in the algorithm." },
