      { type: "p", text: "Result. Conversion improves without increasing traffic." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Example two. A systems heavy roguelike with limited organic reach" },
      { type: "p", text: "Early players enjoy the depth. Mechanics are solid. Organic discovery is low." },
      { type: "p", text: "Diagnosis. Positioning focuses on systems complexity instead of player fantasy. The page assumes genre knowledge." },
      { type: "p", text: "System adjustment. Translate systems into outcomes. Show moments of power, failure, and progression. Use short clips that highlight those moments repeatedly." },
      { type: "p", text: "Result. Organic discovery improves while maintaining relevance." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Example three. A multiplayer game with festival dependent wishlists" },
      { type: "p", text: "Each festival brings a spike, then a drop." },
      { type: "p", text: "Diagnosis. No continuity around festivals. Players wishlist during the event but disengage afterward." },
      { type: "p", text: "System adjustment. Create a simple rhythm. Tease festival participation. Be active during the event. Follow up with a clear update showing what is next." },
      { type: "p", text: "Result. Spikes turn into plateaus instead of declines." },
      { type: "h2", text: "How to support organic steam wishlist growth without burnout" },
      { type: "p", text: "Sustainable marketing protects development focus. The goal is predictable momentum, not constant activity." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Build one repeatable content format" },
      { type: "p", text: "Choose a format that consistently shows the game well." },
      { type: "p", text: "Short gameplay loops. Feature focused clips. Before and after comparisons." },
      { type: "p", text: "Repetition reduces effort and increases clarity." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Connect updates to a clear reason to wishlist" },
      { type: "p", text: "Every update should answer why now matters." },
      { type: "p", text: "What changed. Why it improves the experience. Why this moment is relevant." },
      { type: "p", text: "This keeps intent high." },
      { type: "h3", text: "Track quality and behavior, not just volume" },
      { type: "p", text: "Watch what happens after the wishlist." },
      { type: "p", text: "Do users play the demo. Do they follow updates. Do they return to the page." },
      { type: "p", text: "These signals matter more than daily totals." },
      { type: "h2", text: "Key takeaways for experienced indie developers" },
      { type: "p", text: "Steam wishlist marketing is not about tricks or volume. It is about systems." },
      { type: "p", text: "Organic steam wishlist growth stalls when positioning is unclear, pages do not convert, discovery lacks continuity, or early audiences are misaligned." },
      { type: "p", text: "When these elements work together, wishlist growth becomes steadier and less stressful." },
      { type: "p", text: "For teams already deep into development, this approach turns marketing from a constant reaction into a structured process." },
      { type: "h2", text: "A calm next step if you want clarity" },
      { type: "p", text: "If you want an outside perspective, a focused review of your Steam page and wishlist flow can often reveal why organic growth is stalling and where effort is being lost. A clear diagnosis is sometimes all that is needed to restore momentum." },
